I didn't plan my way into a working system. I picked something I actually needed to do, prepping a meeting, and worked through it with whatever I had. The AI got things wrong. It missed context I assumed it had. But that wasn't failure, it was the system telling me what to build next.

Every useful capability grew from one of those moments. [[let-structure-emerge|Structure emerged]] from real friction, not from planning.
